dismissalText.commentary: Shafali Verma run out (Mlaba/†Jafta) 205 (197b 23x4 8x6 288m) SR: 104.06

dismissalComment.html: Terrible mix-up. Rodrigues comes down the track to a full delivery outside off and taps this to mid-on. Shafali hesitated a bit and was blocked by the bowler but decided to take the run. Rodrigues is already at the non-striker's end. Keeper Jafta is quick to collect the ball and take the bails off. Replays confirm that Shafali is short of the crease. The Chidamabaram Stadium gives a loud cheer as she walks out

dismissalText.commentary: Smriti Mandhana c Dercksen b Tucker 149 (161b 27x4 1x6 197m) SR: 92.54

dismissalComment.html: edged and South Africa finally have a wicket! Mandhana falls a run short of 150! Fizzed through on a length just outside off. Mandhana, perhaps knowing what she needs to get to 150, pokes at it with an open bat face. The ball straightens just enough and takes the outside edge. Dercksen swoops down sharply and completes the catch. Smiles in the South African camp; Mandhana, meanwhile, walks off to a standing ovation from her teammates and the crowd. An innings of the highest order!

dismissalComment.html: massive appeal, and given! Reviewed straightaway! Darted in full on middle and leg. Ghosh, like she did in the last over, tries the sweep. Seems to miss this one, though, and gets rapped on the pads. Mlaba goes up, and so does the umpire's finger. This looked pretty adjacent, unless Ghosh has hit it. Seemed to straighten a touch too after pitching. There are murmurs on UltraEdge but nothing when the ball is next to the bat. All eyes on Ball Tracking now...and it reckons the ball would have thundered into leg stump. It took an awful while to build, but when it did, it signalled the end for Ghosh in this innings! And it looks like India have declared their innings too!

dismissalText.commentary: Sune Luus lbw b Sharma 65 (164b 6x4 1x6 201m) SR: 39.63

dismissalComment.html: massive appeal, and Luus has to go this time! Back of a length, pitches on off and then spins back in. Luus, like she has been content to do for much of this session, stays back and tries to defend. The ball, though, spins just enough to go past the inside edge and rap her on the pads. Seems pretty adjacent but Luus wants to have another look. No bat involved and the ball struck her on the back pad. This could be curtains for Luus. And indeed it is. Ball Tracking reckons it would have smashed into middle stump, two-thirds of the way up. Big wicket for India!

dismissalText.commentary: Anneke Bosch lbw b Sharma 9 (18b 2x4 0x6 28m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: that has kept awfully low, and Bosch has to walk back! Back of length on middle and off, and this almost rolls along the ground. Bosch, like she did the previous ball, stays back but when the ball does not bounce, that usually signals the end. Sneaks under the bat as Bosch hurriedly stabs down on it and smacks her right in front of middle and leg on the back pad. The umpire has no qualms in raising her finger, and Bosch does not bother with the review either. Wry smile on her face, nothing she could have done to prevent this!

dismissalComment.html: Harmanpreet goes through Luus, and she is absolutely chuffed! This is the breakthrough India wanted! Back of a length just outside off. Luus has been going back to that length all day long and does so again. The only danger to that ploy, though, is when the ball skids on and keeps low. This does exactly that and Luus, trying to hurriedly hack it to leg, is beaten for pace. Clips the outside of off stump, and Luus walks back, to a standing ovation from her teammates!

dismissalComment.html: another vociferous appeal, and this time, the finger goes up! Length on middle and leg, and Wolvaardt goes back. Wolvaardt has been doing that all innings but on this occasion, the ball skids on a little quicker than she anticipates. Keeps a touch low too and beats her on the flick. Gets pinned on the pads in front of leg stump and Gayathri Venugopalan had no hesitation raising her finger. Wolvaardt has reviewed, though. Was it heading down leg? No bat involved and Ball Tracking has the ball thumping into leg stump. India are elated; Wolvaardt, after a stellar knock, has to walk back!
